      "writtenOn": "2020-09-08T18:45:44Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Out of curiosity, why is this defined on GrCaps and not GrRenderTargetProxy, like:\n\n   GrRenderTargetProxy::getDstSampleType(const GrCaps\u0026);\n\nThe only cap that is checked appears to be texture barrier support, everything else uses functions defined on the render target proxy, although the logic does differ for each backend. Is that why it\u0027s on caps instead? To easily use per-backend logic?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 387,
        "startChar": 20,
        "endLine": 387,
        "endChar": 44
      },
      "revId": "f886d4cab1080d9ed53b7c76c6af35c41ec4bb4a",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d837cc9c_dd28f605",
        "filename": "src/gpu/GrCaps.h",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 387,
      "author": {
        "id": 5036
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-09-08T19:44:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah it is to allow the backends to have different logic on what DstSampleType they use. Like we need to know that when on vulkan if the proxy doesn\u0027t have the input flag, but isn\u0027t a texture that we still can\u0027t use the GrDstSampleType::kSelfTexture. We could of course add more caps checks like doesSupportSelfTexture(), but I just worry once we try to start putting metal and d3d into this as well it will get real messy trying to write something in GrRenderTargetProxy that correctly checks and prioritizes approaches for each backend.",
      "parentUuid": "4a9ad7e4_ebfc2739",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 387,
        "startChar": 20,
        "endLine": 387,
        "endChar": 44
      },
